## Gamification Mechanics (Ethical Implementation)

### Mechanic 1: Discipline Streaks (Not Trading Streaks)

**Traditional gamification:** "Trade 10 days in a row — get a badge!" (encourages overtrading)  
**Winzinvest version:** "Followed your stops 30 days straight — Discipline Master"

```typescript
// Dashboard widget
<DisciplineStreak
  currentStreak={30}
  longestStreak={45}
  metric="days_without_override"
  message="You haven't overridden a stop in 30 days. This is the edge."
/>
```

**Color coding:**
- 🟢 Green: 30+ day streak (elite discipline)
- 🟡 Yellow: 7-29 days (building habit)
- 🔴 Red: <7 days or recent override (reset, no shame)

**Anti-shame:** Don't say "You broke your streak!" Say "New streak started. What changed?"

---

### Mechanic 2: Rejected Trade Log (Loss Avoidance Visibility)

**Core Drive 8 (Loss & Avoidance)** is Winzinvest's superpower. Make it visible.

**Implementation:**

```typescript
// Dashboard section
<RejectedTradesCard
  title="Trades You Didn't Take"
  subtitle="System blocked these setups. Here's why."
  trades={[
    { symbol: 'TSLA', reason: 'Sector exposure at 32% (limit: 30%)', wouldHaveLost: '$1,200' },
    { symbol: 'NVDA', reason: 'Conviction 0.38 (floor: 0.40)', wouldHaveLost: '$800' },
  ]}
  totalSaved="$2,000 (estimated)"
/>
```

**Why this works:**
- Satisfies curiosity (variable reward)
- Reinforces system value (I'm protected)
- Creates "near miss" feeling (I almost took that bad trade)

**Update monthly with backtest:** Run rejected signals through outcomes to show "would have lost $X."

---

### Mechanic 3: Mastery Levels (Competence)

Instead of arbitrary badges, tie progression to **actual understanding** of the system.

**3-Tier Skill Path:**

| Level | Unlock Criteria | Access |
|---|---|---|
| **Novice** | Default | Pre-filtered signals, auto-execution, dashboard in simple mode |
| **Practitioner** | 30 days active + PMF survey + journal 10+ entries | See all signals (not just high conviction), manual gate overrides (with confirmation) |
| **Expert** | 90 days + D7 activation + 60-day discipline streak | Parameter tuning, custom screeners, advanced analytics |

**Implementation:**

```typescript
// User model
model User {
  masteryLevel String @default("novice") // novice | practitioner | expert
  masteryUnlockedAt DateTime?
}

// Dashboard shows current level and progress to next
<MasteryProgress
  currentLevel="practitioner"
  nextLevel="expert"
  progress={[
    { requirement: '90 days active', completed: true },
    { requirement: 'D7 activation', completed: true },
    { requirement: '60-day discipline streak', completed: false, current: 42 },
  ]}
/>
```

**Why levels matter:**
- Novice: System is protective (hides complexity, prevents mistakes)
- Expert: System is collaborative (exposes internals, allows tuning)

This matches user skill growth. Don't give advanced controls to new users.

