## Ethical Checklist for New Features

Before adding any gamification or personalization mechanic, ask:

- [ ] Does this encourage **more trading** or **better discipline**?
- [ ] Does this create FOMO or urgency to trade? (If yes, kill it)
- [ ] Does this compare users to each other in a competitive way? (If yes, anonymize)
- [ ] Does this use variable rewards tied to **trade outcomes**? (If yes, that's gambling)
- [ ] Does this satisfy intrinsic motivation (autonomy, mastery, relatedness)?
- [ ] Would the FCA flag this as harmful? (Read the research)

**Safe zone:**
- Progress toward discipline
- Mastery of system features
- Loss avoidance visibility
- Community learning (not competition)

**Danger zone:**
- Trading frequency rewards
- P&L leaderboards
- Notifications about "opportunities"
- Celebratory animations for completed trades

