## Summary: The Winzinvest Gamification Philosophy

> **"We gamify discipline, not trading. Every mechanic should make users trade LESS, not more."**

### Core Principles

1. **Reward restraint** (blocked trades), not action (completed trades)
2. **Show progress toward calmness**, not excitement
3. **Celebrate long-term discipline streaks**, not short-term wins
4. **Avoid social comparison** on performance (causes harm)
5. **Personalize to reduce friction** (onboarding, dashboard), not increase engagement (notifications)

### Quick Reference

| Framework | Key Insight | Winzinvest Application |
|---|---|---|
| **Octalysis** | 8 core drives of motivation | Loss & Avoidance (CD8) is primary; Development (CD2) secondary |
| **Hook Model** | Trigger → Action → Variable Reward → Investment | Internal trigger = anxiety; Reward = seeing trades you didn't take |
| **Fogg B=MAP** | Behavior = Motivation × Ability × Prompt | Time prompts for high-motivation moments (after system saves user) |
| **SDT** | Autonomy, Competence, Relatedness | User controls rules (autonomy), sees mastery progress (competence), Founding Member community (relatedness) |

